heaviest_rainfall.status: 36.8mm of rain was recorded as having fallen on 04 January 2025, marking an exceptional 37.2 hour precipitation event.  At times the rain was falling at 4.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The 10th ranked rain rate was recorded today with a peak rate of 10.1mm per hour, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  9.37mm of rain fell during the storm's 16.6 hours length.  The heaviest rain was recorded on 02 September 2025 with a peak rate of 27.0mm per hour.  The storm lasted 15.0 hours and had a total rainfall of 21.19mm.

longest_rain.status: The storm today ranked 10th for the length of the storm when compared to others in our records and it lasted 16.6 hours.  9.37mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 10.1mm per hour.  The record duration for continuous rain was set on 04 January 2025, the storm lasted 37.2 hours with a total precipitation of 36.8mm and it reached 4.6mm per hour at times.
